# Obsidian Plugin Project Structure

- Entry point is [`main.ts`](mdc:main.ts). It compiles to `main.js` which Obsidian loads.
- Build with npm + esbuild; scripts in [`package.json`](mdc:package.json), config in [`esbuild.config.mjs`](mdc:esbuild.config.mjs).
- Required release artifacts at plugin root: `main.js`, [`manifest.json`](mdc:manifest.json), optional [`styles.css`](mdc:styles.css).
- Source should be organized under `src/` when expanding beyond a single file. Keep `main.ts` minimal (plugin lifecycle and command registration) and move logic into modules (e.g., `src/settings.ts`, `src/commands/*`, `src/utils/*`).
- Do not commit build artifacts or `node_modules/`.

## Common commands
- Install: `npm install`
- Dev (watch): `npm run dev`
- Production build: `npm run build`